<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-05-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-05-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="877" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d877">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">818.00/974</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at San José</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Chase</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                            José</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-05-07"><hi rend="italic">May 7,
                                    1920</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received May 19.]</dateline>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 772</seg></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>:</p>
                            <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                            <p>A Bill was introduced in congress and referred to a specially elected
                                commission for examination providing for the trial of Tinoco and his
                                adherents for military rebellion and declaring his acts during the
                                time from January 27, 1917 to September 3, 1919, as null and void,
                                with exceptions for the exclusive benefit of the Treasury. …</p>
                            <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                            <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Benjamin F.
                                Chase</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>